1 packet Beef Eye Round
1 tomato
1 cucumber
1 bag salad leaves
1 drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 packet Italian Truffle Mayonnaise
1 packet Roasted Potatoes with Garlic Herb Butter
olive oil

• Place beef between two sheets of baking paper. Pound with rolling pin until slightly flattened (this ensures it’s extra tender!)
• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over high heat. Season beef
• Cook beef for 2-3 mins each side or until cooked to your liking
• Transfer to a plate

• Meanwhile, prick a few holes in the potato packet and microwave until soft and steaming, 4-5 mins
• Chop tomato. Thinly slice cucumber

• In a bowl, combine tomato, cucumber and salad leaves
• Drizzle with olive oil and balsamic vinegar, season and toss
• Slice steak
• Plate up potatoes and steak. Serve with salad and truffle mayo